    <div class="md-modal md-effect-11" id="site-7">
        <div class="md-content">
            <div class="sitepoint-image">
                <img src="content/img/map/stpauls.jpg" alt="St Paul's Cathedral" />
            </div>
            <div class="sitepoint-content">
                <h3>St Paul's Cathedral</h3>
                <p class="lead">
                    Well what can you say?! The masterpiece of the genius of Christopher Wren – the architect we traditionally thank for rebuilding London after the Great Fire off 1666, which destroyed two thirds of the medieval city.
                </p>
                <p>The blaze took down the old St Paul's on the same site, and it fell to Wren to build something bigger and better than ever before. We think he did a rather good job! Wren is today buried in the crypt he designed. Blink and you miss him though – a small square plaque on the floor. But it’s the crafty epitaph, "Reader, if you seek my monument, look around you" which gives Wren the last laugh!</p>
                <p>Home to some of the biggest public ceremonies including Charles and Diana's wedding in 1981 to Margaret Thatcher's funeral in 2013.</p>
                <p>Climb to the top of the dome to stand 365 feet over London (one foot for every day of the year) and it’s hard not to appreciate the rich and diverse architecture we are so lucky to have.</p>
            </div>
