    <div class="md-modal md-effect-11" id="site-10">
        <div class="md-content">
            <div class="sitepoint-image">
                <img src="content/img/map/shakespeare.jpg" alt="Shakespeare's Globe" />
            </div>
            <div class="sitepoint-content">
                <h3>Shakespeare's Globe</h3>
                <p class="lead">
                    Ah, Shakespeare's Globe, the only building in London today since the Great Fire of 1666 that is allowed by law a thatch roof in its construction.
                </p>
                <p>In that sense, this is a real snapshot of Tudor London and a visit here is not only a chance to see Shakespeare at it's very best, but also to immerse yourself in an environment where his plays were performed for the first time. Unfortunately this is not the original. The first Globe theatre was destroyed in 1613. We wanted to celebrate the King's arrival to a show and we thought what better way in a wooden and thatch building than to fire a load of cannons.</p>
                <p>What could possibly go wrong?! Yes you guessed it - we burnt it down. It was really embarrassing! 400 years later this exact replica was the work of the American actor Sam Wannamaker.</p>
                <p>Unfortunately he never saw it completed in 1997 but it is a hugely valued and now iconic part of London's famous South Bank and with tickets as little as £5 you'd be mad not to indulge in a little culture from this country's greatest ever playwright.</p>
            </div>
