            <div class="sitepoint-content">
                <h3>London Bridge</h3>
                <p class="lead">
                    The current version of London Bridge was designed by engineer John Rennie and completed by his son (of the same name) over a seven-year period from 1824 to 1831.
                </p>
                <p>The Bridge was constructed from Dartmoor granite, with a length of 928 feet and a width of 49 feet. It was widened in 1902-1904 in an attempt to combat London's chronic traffic congestion.</p>
